Barcelona and Atletico Madrid squads for today’s LaLiga tie have been confirmed. Barcelona manager, Xavi Hernández, named a 23-man squad to tackle Atletico Madrid at Camp Nou. The 23 players are: Ter Stegen, Dest, Piqué, R. Araujo, Sergio, Riqui Puig, O. Dembélé, Dani Alves, Adama, Braithwaite, Neto, Nico, Pedri, L. De Jong, Jordi Alba, Ferran, F. De Jong, O. Mingueza, Aubameyang, Jutglà, Gavi, Ez Abde and Arnau Tenas. On his part, Atletico Madrid boss, Diego Simeone, named a 19-man squad to face Barcelona. The 19 players include: Lecomte, Oblak, Gimenez, Renan Lodi, Savic, Wass, Felipe, Hermoso, Reinildo, Vrsaljko, De Paul, Koke, Lemar, Herrera, Carrasco, Joao Felix, Suarez, Correa and Cunha. Barcelona are currently in the fifth position on the LaLiga table with one point behind Atletico Madrid, who occupy the fourth position. The kick-off time for the Barcelona vs Atletico Madrid match is 4:15 pm.